urgettes - Zucchine farcite","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 courgettes, large"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"90 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"60 g bread, torn in pieces"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"15 g fresh mint leaves"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"120 g red onions, quartered"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"12 green olives, pitted"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"¼ tsp ground black pepper"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 medium eggs"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g ricotta cheese"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","1585 kJ \/ 380 kcal","23.5 g","13.5 g","24 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Courgettes, from the French word <i>courge<\/i>, meaning 'squash', are a summer squash that is harvested before it is fully grown. For this recipe, the insides have been hollowed out before being stuffed with familiar Italian ingredients: creamy ricotta, fresh mint and salty olives. Topped with breadcrumbs and baked in the oven, these stuffed courgettes are a deliciously light and flavoursome main.","To make this recipe suitable for vegetarians, substitute the Parmesan cheese for a vegetarian hard cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","4 portions"]}